==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mu meson
<hw>mu meson</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>an elementary particle with a negative charge
and a half-life of 2 microseconds; the muon. It is a <isa>lepton</isa>,
not a true meson, and decays to an electron and neutrino and
antineutrino.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> muon, negative muon.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mumm</ent>⟦br⟧
